					<div class="bio">
						<h4>Svetlana Satchkova</h4>
												<p>Svetlana Satchkova is a Russian-born journalist and novelist who immigrated to the United States in 2016. She covers culture and politics, with bylines in the <em>Rumpus</em>, <em>Newsweek</em>, <em>LARB</em>, the <em>Independent</em>, and others. Currently a research fellow at the Jordan Center for the Advanced Study of Russia at NYU, she holds an MFA from Brooklyn College and lives in Brooklyn. Svetlana has published three novels in Russian; her English-language debut, <em>The Undead: A Novel of Modern Russia</em>, was released in January 2026.</p>
